{"content":"---\ntitle: \"&lt;states&gt; of &lt;activityStateQuery&gt; | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.prod: \".net-framework\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"reference\"\nms.assetid: a7cc2018-2b79-44f1-825a-bb7ca08690a3\ncaps.latest.revision: 5\nauthor: \"Erikre\"\nms.author: \"erikre\"\nmanager: \"erikre\"\n---\n# &lt;states&gt; of &lt;activityStateQuery&gt;\nA collection of configuration elements that contain the states of the subscribed activity for which a tracking record should be emitted.  \n  \n For more information on tracking profile queries, see [Tracking Profiles](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md).  \n  \n \\<system.serviceModel>  \n\\<tracking>  \n\\<trackingProfile>  \n\\<workflow>  \n\\<activityStateQueries>  \n\\<activityStateQuery>  \n\\<states>  \n  \n## Syntax  \n  \n```vb  \n<tracking>   <trackingProfile name=\"Name\">       <workflow>          <activityStateQueries>             <activityStateQuery activityName=\"String\" />                <states>                   <state name=\"String\"/>                </states>          </activityStateQueries>       </workflow>   </trackingProfile></tracking>  \n```  \n  \n## Attributes and Elements  \n The following sections describe attributes, child elements, and parent elements.  \n  \n### Attributes  \n None.  \n  \n### Child Elements  \n  \n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<state>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/state-of-states.md)|A configuration element that contains the states of the subscribed activity for which a tracking record should be emitted.|  \n  \n### Parent Elements  \n  \n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<activityStateQuery>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/activitystatequery.md)|Represents a configuration element that is used to track requests to cancel a child activity by the parent activity. The query is necessary for a tracking participant to subscribe to cancel request record objects.|  \n  \n## Remarks  \n One unique feature of an ActivityStateQuery is the ability to extract data when tracking the execution of a workflow. This provides additional context when accessing the tracking records post execution. You can use the [\\<arguments>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/arguments.md), [\\<states>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/states.md) and [\\<states>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/states.md) elements to extract any variable or argument from any activity in a workflow.The following example shows an activity state query that extracts variables and arguments when the activity’s `Closed` tracking record is emitted. Variables and arguments can be extracted only with an ActivityStateRecord and thus are subscribed to within a tracking profile using [\\<activityStateQuery>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/activitystatequery.md).  \n  \n```  \n  \n<activityStateQuery activityName=\"SendEmailActivity\">  \n  <states>  \n    <state name=\"Closed\"/>  \n  </states>  \n  <variables>  \n    <variable name=\"FromAddress\"/>  \n  </variables>  \n  <arguments>  \n    <argument name=\"Result\"/>  \n  </arguments>  \n</activityStateQuery>  \n  \n```  \n  \n## See Also  \n <xref:System.ServiceModel.Activities.Tracking.Configuration.StateElementCollection?displayProperty=fullName>      \n <xref:System.Activities.Tracking.ActivityStateQuery?displayProperty=fullName>       \n [Workflow Tracking and Tracing](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/workflow-tracking-and-tracing.md)   \n [Tracking Profiles](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[12,73],"content":"&lt;states&gt; of &lt;activityStateQuery&gt; | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>states<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> of <ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;lt;</ph>activityStateQuery<ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph> | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,61],"source":"&lt;states&gt; of &lt;activityStateQuery&gt; | Microsoft Docs"}]},{"pos":[340,384],"content":"&lt;states&gt; of &lt;activityStateQuery&gt;","linkify":"&lt;states&gt; of &lt;activityStateQuery&gt;","nodes":[{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>states<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> of <ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;lt;</ph>activityStateQuery<ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph>","pos":[0,44],"source":"&lt;states&gt; of &lt;activityStateQuery&gt;"}]},{"content":"A collection of configuration elements that contain the states of the subscribed activity for which a tracking record should be emitted.","pos":[385,521]},{"pos":[528,682],"content":"For more information on tracking profile queries, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Tracking Profiles<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md)</ept>.","source":"For more information on tracking profile queries, see [Tracking Profiles](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md)."},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>system.serviceModel&gt;","pos":[689,711],"source":"\\<system.serviceModel>"},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>tracking&gt;","pos":[714,725],"source":"\\<tracking>"},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>trackingProfile&gt;","pos":[728,746],"source":"\\<trackingProfile>"},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>workflow&gt;","pos":[749,760],"source":"\\<workflow>"},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>activityStateQueries&gt;","pos":[763,786],"source":"\\<activityStateQueries>"},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>activityStateQuery&gt;","pos":[789,810],"source":"\\<activityStateQuery>